cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper focuses on implementing graph algorithms on the Apache Accumulo distributed database. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses two algorithms for counting triangles in graphs. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with distributed processing of graph algorithms on a cloud-based platform. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper discusses the performance of triangle counting algorithms on power law Graph500 graphs, which are commonly used to model social networks. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): Although less likely, this category could be relevant as the paper deals with cloud-based experiments and distributed processing.
